A Model for Gamers' Revenue in Casinos

Description :

   The study by Iyengar, Eliashberg and Hui -- entitled "A Model for
   Gamers' Revenue in Casinos" -- develops a mathematical model which
   integrates gamers' frequency of casino visits, their total wagers and
   the distribution of those bets at table games versus slots machines.
   The researchers determined if revenue from specific players was derived
   from "skill" or "luck," and they were able to identify players who are
   highly skilled or perhaps revenue-producing high rollers.

Droits d'auteur :

   Attribution Non-Commercial (BY-NC)

Formats disponibles

   Téléchargez comme PDF, TXT ou lisez en ligne sur Scribd
