   Mr. Joel le
   >Deroff
   >joel@ilgaeurope.org

   USD
   >68,000.00

   UK, GR,
   >and NL

   International Alert and its project partners, Symbiosis and the
   Commission for
   >Filipino Migrant Workers (CFMW), organized local forums bringing
   together people
   >from minority groups in the UK, Greece, and the Netherlands in order
   to identify
   >key messages to combat sexist, racist and xenophobic speech of
   candidates who
   >are seeking (re)election in 2014. By sending out these messages,
   backed up by
   >facts and statistics, through a variety of different channels (and
   with the help of
   >communication experts) they provided a platform to give voice to
   people who are
   >marginalized from the center of power, making their voices finally
   heard. The
   >project partners also monitored and micro targeted candidates and
   parties who
   >use xenophobic speech and sent messages to their potential opponents.

